  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Resilience through the promotion of Water Harvesting facilities in Benatsemay Woreda of Ay</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	Construction of water harvesting ground catchment with a 100m3 masonry/concrete reservoir, 
&#x2022;	750m2 masonry paved collection area, 
&#x2022;	Silt trap construction 
&#x2022;	Supply and install hand pump
&#x2022;	All the required material mobilization, store &amp; camping construction and construction crew mobilization.
&#x2022;	Training 7 WaSHCO members.
&#x2022;	Preparatory activities such as signing agreement, familiarization, mobilization of human and material resources, etc;
&#x2022;	Organizing training and equipping water management committees and care takers;
&#x2022;	WASH awareness raising for users</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	Improved access to safe water for 2,334 people in the Aymele &#x2018;kebele&#x2019; through construction of one rainwater harvesting scheme 
&#x2022;	Enhancing Wash awareness of Aymele kebele community members through organizing trainigs to one WaSHCO members</narrative>
  </description>
